Greetings ET lovers,

It looks like Peter Pan will be heading to court some time 
soon. 

A Canadian author is taking a British children's hospital to
court over the rights to the fairy tale hero Peter Pan. When
the story's creator James M. Barrie gave the copyright to
London's Great Ormand Street Hospital for Sick Children, it
alloted the care center donations by any director or merchan-
diser who wished to use images of the characters.  

However, author Emily Somma feels that the tale of Peter, 
Wendy, Tinker Bell and Captain Hook belongs to the public and
has filed a suit against the hospital. Book Magazine reports
that the reason Somma is taking such actions is because the
hospital will likely file suit against her to halt the pub-
lication of Somma's "After the Rain: A New Adventure for Peter 
Pan," a story in which Peter Pan is taken away from Neverland 
to grow up. 

Perhaps both sides should take some hints from Peter and grow
up themselves.

That's all folks!
Dante

