              GIBSON RECALLS 'UNEXPLAINABLE' RESCUE

"Signs" star Mel Gibson may not believe in little green men
from outer-space, but that doesn't mean he dismisses the un-
explainable. Talking to reporters in New York about his new
alien drama, Gibson recalled a car accident he had in
Australia when he was 21 that probably should have ended his
life. Explaining how he was "doing about 95 in my little
four-cylinder Ford, little junkbox" from Adelaide to Sydney,
the 47-year-old actor said he drove off a rain-slicked road
while impatiently trying to pass a truck. "So, I swerved
away and there was a truck coming in the other direction,"
Gibson explained. "I'm really cooked here and so I swung
out of the way and lost all control of the steering and it
was just gonna go over the cliff. I remember before I cover-
ed up in a crouch position and let go of the steering wheel
into the hands of the Almighty there was a massive gum tree
coming right at me at a very rapid speed. Just before (the
car) went down over the cliff I covered my head and said a
very short prayer and felt this, 'Bang, boom.' I took my
hands off and the big gum tree was pressed against one side
of the car door and had dented it in. The other side of the
car was a sapling and I had been caught between the two
trees and the front wheels were hanging over the abyss. I
had to crawl over the front seat and get out the back doors
because the front doors were jammed from these two trees."
He concluded: "I kind of thought that was pretty wild to
get caught by a couple of saplings before going over a
cliff, not getting hit by either of the trucks, so some-
body had his hand on me that day. It's things like that
that inform you of something greater than yourself walk-
ing with you."  "Signs" comes to video stores Tuesday. 


